{
  "id": 5179186249465856,
  "name": "Permissions Policy: focus-without-user-activation",
  "summary": "Gives embedders control over programmatic focus from embedded content via the focus-without-user-activation permissions policy. When the policy is denied for a frame, programmatic focus calls (element.focus(), autofocus, window.focus(), dialog.showModal(), and popover focusing) are blocked unless triggered by user activation. User-initiated focus such as clicking or tabbing is never affected.\n\nThe policy can be set via a Permissions-Policy HTTP response header or the iframe allow attribute. Focus delegation is supported: a parent frame that has focus can programmatically pass focus to a child iframe, even if the child has the policy denied, and once a frame has focus it can move focus within its own subtree.",
