  "motivation": "Embedded third-party content such as ads, widgets, and iframes can programmatically steal input focus from the top-level page without any user interaction, silently redirecting keystrokes and creating security and accessibility problems. This was originally reported by engineers working on advertising security for large publishers.\n\nToday developers have no reliable way to prevent it: the sandbox attribute disables JavaScript entirely, breaking most embedded content, and JavaScript focus-reclaiming hacks using blur listeners or polling are unreliable, cause visible focus flickering, and do not scale across multiple iframes. This policy provides fine-grained, declarative control over programmatic focus from embedded content.",
